<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 19 at 7:19PM EST  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>Lake effect showers will continue to move across the central
Mohawk Valley, Schoharie Valley, Helderbergs, the greater Capital
District including the Saratoga and Glens Falls areas, northern
and central Taconics into the Berkshires this evening. Poor
visibilities and a quick coating of snow will occur particularly
on untreated surfaces in the heavier showers. The activity will
continue to shift southward and weaken as the evening progresses.</description>
